sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: pck
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Harley Greene
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: pck codes for Phosphoenolpyruvate carboxykinase (Pck), a kinase involved in gluconeogenesis in E. coli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: No codons were modified to make this part
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: pck gene came from E coli strain MG1655

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_I752001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Franz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: CheZ is one of the 6 Che proteins used in chemeotaxis. CheZ is a phosphatase which dephosphorylates CheY which in turn then allows the cell to run and tumble, wheres if CheZ is absence, CheY is phosphorylated, and the cell tumbles exclusively. (Topp and Gallivan J. Am. Chem. Soc. 129, p6865-6873)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K1412829
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Characterize efficiency of RBS with chemotaxis
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ruihua Zhang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: BBa_R0010 BBa_B0033 BBa_K629003 BBa_B0015 Plac-RBS(0.01)-CheZ-TT This part can express CheZ protein which decide the E.coli whether tumble of swim straight.In return, we can charecterize the efficiency of RBS and Promoter by measure the distance E.coli migration. 3H:13-P3-3H BBa_R0010 2L:14-P2-2L BBa_B0033 18G:14-P1-18G BBa_K629003 4F:13-P3-4F BBa_B0015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: 1.link RBS and Promoter is too short to link to other gene part.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K557000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: CheZ: phosphatase which dephosphorylates CheY-P and thus plays an important role in E.Coli chemotaxi
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Yinghong Lan
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part encodes CheZ, which is a phosphatase which dephosphorylates CheY-P and causes the flagellum to rotate counterclockwise. E.coli lacking the cheZ gene cannot dephosphorylate CheY-P, tumble incessantly, and are thus nonmotile while inducing the expression of CheZ can restore motility in a CheZ knockout strain by reactivating wild-type chemotaxis.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We get it from the genome of Top10 by PCR.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The genome of Top10, a strain of E.coli

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K094100
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Liu Chenli
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part contains the cheZ operon coding region without an rbs nor a terminator. cheZ protein is responsible for the dephosphorylation of cheY protein in bacteria flagella movement.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part is without promoter, rbs or terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The origin of the cheZ gene comes from E. Coli strain MG1655 chromosome.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283020
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: W Ling , Nelson Chu, Shi Lei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consist of a chez protein linked to a double terminator. The cheZ protein is responsible for the dephosphorylation of cheY protein in bacteria flagella movement. The chez coding region has a 6-Histidine tail and do not contain any rbs.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The chez-histag coding region is self-designed The double terminator is from the registry

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: trz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Fusion protein Trg-EnvZ for signal transduction
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Valencia iGEM 2006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: We created a hybrid gene coding for a protein in which Trg (chemoreceptor) contributed its periplasmic and transmembrane domains as well as a short cytoplasmic segment and EnvZ (osmosensor) contributed its cytoplasmic kinase/phosphatase domain.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: cheZ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: cheZ, chemotaxis regulator, protein phosphatase for CheY
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Zilong WANG, Yi ZHENG
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Polar localization is dependent on CheA-short. CheZ is a cytosolic phosphatase which functions in the chemotaxis signal transduction complex. Plays an important role in bacterial chemotaxis signal transduction pathway by accelerating the dephosphorylation of phosphorylated CheY (CheY-P).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: how to control the proper expression of cheZ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: genome of E. Coli BL21 plys strain

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: tar-envZ
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Stephen Lee, Roshan Kumar, Joe Levine, Ziyan Chu (Polkadorks, IAP 2004)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
Coding sequence for Tar-EnvZ fusion protein. Tar is the bacterial chemotaxis receptor for aspartate. EnvZ is an osmosensor kinase, which, through phosphorylation of OmpR, regulates transcription of porin genes.
This fusion protein combines the extracellular and transmembrane domains of Tar with the intracellular domain of EnvZ. The fusion converts chemical binding of aspartate to production of transcription factors.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: A silent point mutation was made at base 423 (A -> C) to eliminate an XbaI restriction enzyme site. The mutation was designed to match codons with similar frequencies of usage in E. coli.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118015
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: glgC coding sequence encoding ADP-glucose pyrophosphorylase
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of ''glgC'' from ''Escherichia coli'' JM109. It encodes ADP-glucose pyrophosphorylase, which catalyses Glucose 1-phosphate + ATP -> ADP-glucose + PPi, a step in the production of glycogen from glucose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The genomic DNA sequence contains to EcoRI sites, both of which have been mutated out using the mutagenesis by blunt-ended ligation (MABEL) technique

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K819009
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xing Wenmin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: cheZ ligated to a weak promoter. This part express CheZ protein weakly and will induce weak mobility in delta cheZ E.coli strain.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: There is a point mutation at position 56 of CheZ coding sequence with have little effect to its function and the bases corresponding to stop codon is changed to bases coding a more frequently used stop codon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The promoter used here is from Partsregistry. The CheZ gene is from E.coli strain MG1655 by colony PCR and aligned with CheZ sequence at EcoGene database.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K136046
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: alexandra bouaziz
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: EnvZ* is a transmenbrane kinase that phosphorylates ompR the natural inhibitor of pFlhDC independently of any outer signal.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: bacterial genome of mutated (I281S) strain for EnvZ.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118016
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of ''glgC'' (ADP-glucose pyrophosphorylase) from ''Escherichia coli'' JM109 with the substitution G336D. This mutation is known to cause increased activity of ADP-glucose pyrophosphorylase in the absence of the activator fructose 1,6-bisphosphate (FBP), high affinity for FBP and substrates lower affinity for the inhibitor AMP. (Leung ''et al'', 1986; Meyer ''et al.'', 1988)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The mutation G336D was achieved by the substitution of A for G at position 1076 (codon GGC->GAC) by MABEL.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K932000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Sean Kearney
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part promotes the constitutive expression of the curli cluster (csgD), proteins involved in cell-cell adhesion.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: This part regulates curli expression within the cell via transcriptional activation. The construct can be repressed in the presence of the TetR repressor.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Comes from the E. coli K-12 genome.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K283008
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: W Ling , Nelson Chu, Shi Lei
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part consists of a chez coding region followed by a 6-Histidine tail

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: VanBP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Synthetic periplasmic binding protein that docks a vanillin molecule
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Valencia iGEM 2006

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K147000
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Roxanne Shank
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: The cheZ motility protein is a protein kinase which dephosphorylates cheY. cheY regulates the clockwise and counterclockwise rotation of the motor flagella. If cheY is phosphorylated the motor flagella are not in sync and the bacterium tumbles. If cheY is not phosphorylated the motor flagella are in sync and the bacterium runs (often towards a chemoattractant)

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: lsrK
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Robert Cool
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part codes for the protein LsrK which phosphorylates AI-2 which acts to promote the lsrA promoter.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This sequence is found in the E. coli strain MG1655.
